column2: is the PMBOK part of the learner kit or is that a separate purchase?  If so, do I need to purchase both?

column2: is the PMBOK part of the learner kit or is that a separate purchase?  If so, do I need to purchase both?
column5:
The PMBOK is not included in the Learner Kit. If you have access to our online books on your training site, we do have the PMBOK Guide Sixth Edition available. 

In addition, if you are planning to sit for the exam in the next year, I would suggest becoming a PMI member as you will get a $150 USD off the exam fee and you will be able to download your own copy of the PMBOK Guide Sixth and Seventh Editions. For details:

https://www.pmi.org/membership

column2: I couldn't get into the session for 25 mins. Do I have to repeat this session?

column2: What is the difference b/n end users & customers? (if it's not off topic)
column5: What is the difference b/n end users & customers? (if it's not off topic)

column2: What is the difference b/n end users & customers? (if it's not off topic)
column5:
In some cases, the end user and customer may be the same person or organization, but in other cases, they may be different. 

An end user is the person who will actually use a product or service. For example, in software development, the end user is the person who will use the software application.

A customer is the person or organization that pays for the product or service. For example, the customer may be a company that buys software for its employees to use, but the end users are the individual employees who use the software.

column2: What is the difference between SEAM and RACI?
column5:
SEAM stands for Situation, Evidence, Analysis, and Recommendations. It is a method used to analyze and evaluate the current state of a process or system and to identify areas for improvement.

RACI, on the other hand, stands for Responsible, Accountable, Consulted, and Informed. It is a matrix used to assign roles and responsibilities within a project or process. The RACI matrix helps to ensure that everyone involved in a project or process understands their role and responsibilities.

column2: Sorry I just dropped out, can you send me your response to this question again?
column5:
SEAM is a tool used to assess the level of engagement and importance of different stakeholders in a project or initiative. The matrix helps to prioritize engagement efforts and allocate resources effectively by considering the level of influence and interest each stakeholder has in the project.

RACI, on the other hand, is a matrix used to assign roles and responsibilities within a project or process. The RACI matrix helps to ensure that everyone involved in a project or process understands their role and responsibilities. The four elements of the matrix are: Responsible, Accountable, Consulted, and Informed.

column2: Is scrum master a servant leader??
column5: Is scrum master a servant leader??

column2: Is scrum master a servant leader??
column5: In my opinion, I would say that a Scrum Master can be considered a servan leader. In Scrum, the role of the Scrum Master is to facilitate and support the development team and other stakeholders in their adoption of the Scrum framework. This involves removing obstacles, facilitating discussions and decision-making, and promoting collaboration and communication.
